lyrics:
[Verse]
In the heat of the south, where the grass is green
I light up a joint, just a smokin' fiend
Alone in a field, where the sky's so high
Blowin' smoke rings as the clouds roll by

[Chorus]
Just me and Mary Jane in this wide-open space
With the wind in my hair, and a smile on my face
Smokin' weed alone, feelin' so free
Lost in the moment, no one but me
